        ],
        "text": "سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ الرَّجُلِ يُوجَدُ قَتِيلًا فِي الْقَرْيَةِ أَوْ بَيْنَ قَرْيَتَيْنِ فَقَالَ يُقَاسُ مَا بَيْنَهُمَا فَأَيُّهُمَا كَانَتْ أَقْرَبَ ضُمِّنَتْ ."
      },
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": {
          "segments": [
            "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Usman Bin Isa, from Sama’at Bin Mahran, ",
            "(The narrator) says, ‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the man who was found killed in the town, or in between two towns. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It would be compared what is between the two, so whichever of the two was nearer, would be responsible’."
          ],
          "text": "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from Usman Bin Isa, from Sama’at Bin Mahran,\n\n(The narrator) says, ‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the man who was found killed in the town, or in between two towns. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It would be compared what is between the two, so whichever of the two was nearer, would be responsible’."
        }
